emuInput.TitMainTitle: Groom Detroit Prince and bride Jessie Jackson Prince, standing behind table with three tiered wedding cake, in Jackson home on Gerritt Street
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 11, 1961, pg. 16 reads: "Cutting Cake - Miss Jessie Jackson of Pittsburgh was united in marriage to Detroit Prince of Florida, recently. The Rev. J.C. Hairston performed the ceremony in bride's home on Gerritt St.  The newlyweds are shown cutting their wedding cake at the reception that followed the rites. - Harris Photo."
